The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 20 December is 12,016 (1,390.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 15 December, there were 1,306 new confirmed cases (151.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 December, there were 699 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 87% (607 extra cases).
